https://github.com/cloudpanel-io/vhost-templates/tree/master/v1/

O que fazem os templates Vhost?

Eles criam scripts de configuração básicos para cada domínio:

Exemplo de Document Root: /home/cloudpanel/htdocs/dominio.com
    Vhost file for NGINX: /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/dominio.com.conf
    NGINX Access and Error Log file:
        /home/cloudpanel/logs/dominio.com/nginx/access.log
        /home/cloudpanel/logs/dominio.com/nginx/error.log
    PHP-FPM Error Log file:
        /home/cloudpanel/logs/dominio.com/php/error.log
    A self-signed TLS certificate

The right Vhost Template for your Application is essential. For managing the CloudPanel Vhost Templates we are using GitHub. Vhost Templates for all popular PHP Applications can be found there.

O tempalte Vhost correto para seu aplicativo é essencial. Para gerenciar os templates Vhost do CloudPanel, usamos o GitHub. Os tempaltes Vhost para todos os aplicativos PHP populares podem ser encontrados aqui https://vhost-templates.cloudpanel.io/v1/.


Adding an Application#

The Vhost Templates are organized within Applications. The Vhost Template for newer application versions may be different than for an older one.

Para adicionar novos tempaltes de Aplicativos siga os passos:

1) Login into the CloudPanel as User with admin rights.

2) Go to the Admin Area by clicking on Admin Area top right.

3) In the left menu, click on Vhost Templates and click on the button Add Application.

Enter the Application Name and click on the button Add New Application to save.

https://www.cloudpanel.io/docs/cloudpanel-ce/admin-area/vhost-templates

Atualizar os tempaltes VJHost

Faça login no servidor como root e execute

clpctl vhost-templates:import


